<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14317:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-25T00:00:00+03:00">August 25,
                                    1941—12 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 25—11:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1570. I am reliably informed that the Soviet authorities ordered the
                            evacuation of all children from Moscow not later than August 25 and from
                            the suburban area within a radius of approximately 30 miles of the city
                            not later than August 28.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>